# Skill #6 - Create a Database

### Bluehost Portal
Select databases to view and create

![](img/bluehost-portal.jpg)



### Bluehost Databases
* Find the Bluehost database page
* Create a new database named "subscribers"
* Note that my prefix is 'uncobacs', your will be different

```
    Database
    Create New Database
    uncobacs_subscribers
```

### Bluehost Databases
This is where you create a new database

![](img/bluehost-databases.png)


### Database Users
* Create a new database user

```
    MySQL Users
    Add uncobacs_350
    bluehost password
```


### Subscribers User Permissions
* Grant database permissions to new user

```
    Add User
    User: uncobacs_350
    Database: uncobacs_subscribers
```


### Bluehost Database Users
This is where you setup new database users with permissions

![](img/bluehost-datausers.png)


### View Databases
* Make sure that everything looks good

```
    phpMyAdmin
    view databases list
    Databases
    uncobacs_subscribers
```


### Bluehost phpMyAdmin
This is where you work with your databases

![](img/bluehost-phpMyAdmin.png)


### Bluehost Select Your Database
This is where you work with your database

![](img/bluehost-db.png)


### Select the "subscribers" database

```
    Structure
    Create table
    subscribers
```


### Database Structure
View the rows and columns in your tables

* Select subscribers table

![](img/bluehost-structure.png)


### SQL Commands
Execute queries on your database

![](img/bluehost-sql.png)


